wikipedia_page.main: William Wallace Rodger (13 January 1847 – 23 October 1888), known from 1887 William Wallace Rodger-Cunliffe, was an English lawyer, billiards player and first-class cricketer who played for Kent County Cricket Club.

response: Rodger was a cricketer who played one first-class match for Kent County Cricket Club in 1870 after leaving Eton, playing against an MCC side during Canterbury Cricket Week. He scored a total of seven runs in the match.John Rodger, CricInfo. Retrieved 2019-03-30. Although he played some cricket at Oxford he did not make the University XI. He played club cricket for a variety of amateur sides, including MCC, Band of Brothers and the Gentlemen of Kent. His brother, William Rodger, also played for Kent.John Rodger, CricketArchive . Retrieved 2019-03-30.
